<recipe>
    <name>Clam Chowder, East Hampton Style</name>
    <indexCharacter>C</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in a large heavy-bottomed stockpot. Add the onion and cook over medium-low heat for 10 minutes, or until translucent. Add the celery, carrots, potatoes, thyme, salt, and pepper and saute for 10 more minutes. Add the clam juice, bring to a boil, and simmer, uncovered, until the vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes. 

In a small pot, melt the remaining 4 tablespoons of butter and whisk in the flour. Cook over very low heat for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Whisk in a cup of the hot broth and then pour this mixture back into the cooked vegetables. Simmer for a few minutes until the broth is thickened. 

Add the milk and clams and heat gently for a few minutes to cook the clams. Taste for salt and pepper. Serve hot.</instructions>
